#. Tag: para
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:95
#, no-c-format
msgid "To create a degraded array in which some devices are missing, simply give the word <literal>missing</literal> in place of a device name. This causes <command>mdadm</command> to leave the corresponding slot in the array empty."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "When creating a RAID 5 array, <command>mdadm</command> automatically creates a degraded array with an extra spare drive. This is because building the spare into a degraded array is generally faster than resynchronizing the parity on a non-degraded, but not clean, array. You can override this feature with the <literal>--force</literal> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a degraded array might be useful if you want create a RAID, but one of the devices you want to use already has data on it. In that case, you create a degraded array with other devices, copy data from the in-use device to the RAID that is running in degraded mode, add the device into the RAID, then wait while the RAID is rebuilt so that the data is now across all devices. An example of this process is given in the following procedure:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "To create a degraded RAID 1 device <filename>/dev/md0</filename> , using one single drive <filename>/dev/sd1</filename> , enter the following at the command prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;mdadm --create /dev/md0 -l 1 -n 2 /dev/sda1 missing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "The device should be the same size or larger than the device you plan to add to it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the device you want to add to the mirror contains data that you want to move to the RAID array, copy it now to the RAID array while it is running in degraded mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add the device you copied the data from to the mirror. For example, to add <filename>/dev/sdb1</filename> to the RAID, enter the following at the command prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:141
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;mdadm /dev/md0 -a /dev/sdb1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:142
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can add only one device at a time. You must wait for the kernel to build the mirror and bring it fully online before you add another mirror."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:148
#, no-c-format
msgid "Monitor the build progress by entering the following at the command prompt:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;cat /proc/mdstat"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "To see the rebuild progress while being refreshed every second, enter"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_degraded_raid.xml:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;watch -n 1 cat /proc/mdstat"
msgstr ""

